us.phonetic: /v. prəˈsid; n. ˈproʊsid/, (v. prə sēd′; n. prō′sēd)

example.eg: Could you please tell me how to proceed?
example.egtrans: 您能告诉我该怎么行事吗？

example.eg: I'm sorry for interrupting you; please proceed.

trans_examp.trans_cn: 继续进行, 接着（说或做）

example.eg: Please proceed to gate 9 and wait for further instructions.
example.egtrans: 请前往9号登机口，并等候进一步的指示。

example.eg: The driver shook the reins as a signal to the horse to proceed.
example.egtrans: 车夫抖了一下缰绳，示意马继续前进。

trans_examp.trans_cn: 继续向前, 接着做某事

example.eg: If the treatment proceeds normally, the patient will most probably recover.
example.egtrans: 如果治疗继续正常进行下去，病人很可能会康复。

trans_examp.trans_cn: 继续发展, 继续进行下去

example.eg: I would like to proceed with my reading, if you don't mind.
example.egtrans: 如果你不介意的话，我想继续看书。

example.eg: After a slow beginning, the team proceeded to defeat their opponents.
example.egtrans: 比赛开始比较缓慢，接下来这个队伍打败了对手。

example.eg: If you proceed in behaving like this, you will end up in trouble.
example.egtrans: 如果你坚持这样做，会陷入麻烦的。

example.eg: All proceeds from the sale will go to charity.
example.egtrans: 所有销售所得都将捐给慈善机构。

us.phonetic: /v. prəˈsid; n. ˈproʊsid/, (v. prə sēd′; n. prō′sēd)

example.eg: Her delusions proceed directly from her schizophrenia.
example.egtrans: 她的那些错觉是直接由精神分裂症造成的。

us.phonetic: /v. prəˈsid; n. ˈproʊsid/, (v. prə sēd′; n. prō′sēd)

example.eg: When we found out how expensive the goods were, we did not proceed with the order.

trans_examp.trans_cn: 不再继续, 结束, 停止, 取消
